TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi abstract sealed beforefieldinit UnicodeRanges extends System.Object
public ref class UnicodeRanges abstract sealed

Docs.summary: Provides static properties that return predefined instances that correspond to blocks from the Unicode specification.

remarks.format:
## Remarks
You use <xref:System.Text.Unicode.UnicodeRanges> properties to retrieve Unicode named ranges, each of which consists of a contiguous block of Unicode code points. Some ranges include undefined code points. For example, in the **Armenian** Unicode block (U+0530-U+058F), U+0530, U+0557-U+0558, U+0560, U+0588, and U+058B-058C are undefined. One or more undefined code points can occur at the beginning of a range, at the end of a range, or anywhere in between.
Currently, the <xref:System.Text.Unicode.UnicodeRange> class supports only named ranges in the Basic Multilingual Plane (BMP), which extends from U+0000 to U+FFFF.

MemberSignature.Value: Public Shared ReadOnly Property All As UnicodeRange
public: static property System::Text::Unicode::UnicodeRange ^ All { System::Text::Unicode::UnicodeRange ^ get(); };

Docs.summary: Gets a range that consists of the entire Basic Multilingual Plane (BMP), from U+0000 to U+FFFF).
Docs.value: A range that consists of the entire BMP.
